We’ve made several improvements based on your feedback, including fixing overlapping text, grouping Share Certificates in a new section in Accounts, adding Manage Account Display to the Profile (person icon) menu, and making your Accounts screen easier to read by removing unnecessary space and labels. You’ll also find helpful links to our How-To Guides at digitalbanking.schoolsfirstfcu.org throughout.

We’ve made several improvements based on your feedback, including fixing overlapping text, grouping Share Certificates in a new section in Accounts, adding Manage Account Display to the Profile (person icon) menu, and making your Accounts screen easier to read by removing unnecessary space and labels. You’ll also find helpful links to our How-To Guides at digitalbanking.schoolsfirstfcu.org throughout.

We’ve made several improvements based on your feedback, including color-coding debits and credits in your transaction history and displaying loan balances on your Accounts screen. We’ve also fixed overlapping text, and your notes on Member-to-Member transfers are now visible to you and your recipients in transaction details.

Remember to look for links to our How-To Guides throughout the app, or visit them anytime at digitalbanking.schoolsfirstfcu.org/guides.

We've heard your feedback and made several improvements as a result. To streamline logging in, “Remember me” now automatically turns on and stays on when you enable Touch ID or Face ID. Also, your balances now update immediately after you make a transfer. You’ll also enjoy enhancements to how devices with small screens display, how shares display when they are closed, and how transaction notes work.
